<div class="loc article-content">
<div id="article-content_1-0" class="comp article-content mntl-block">
<div id="mntl-sc-page_1-0" class="comp structured-content expert-content mntl-sc-page mntl-block" data-sc-sticky-offset="90" data-sc-ad-label-height="24" data-sc-ad-track-spacing="100" data-sc-min-track-height="250" data-sc-max-track-height="600" data-sc-breakpoint="50em" data-sc-load-immediate="4" data-bind-scroll-on-start="true" data-sc-content-positions="[1, 1050, 1250, 1550, 1950, 2350, 2750, 3150, 3550]">
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0" class="comp theme-generic mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-callout mntl-sc-block-callout mntl-block" data-tracking-id="mntl-sc-block-callout" data-tracking-container="true">
<h3 id="mntl-sc-block-callout-heading_1-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block-callout-heading mntl-text-block">
What to Know</h3><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-callout-heading mntl-text-block -->
<div id="mntl-sc-block-callout-body_1-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block-callout-body mntl-text-block">
<ul><li>For a soft reset, use a working controller to go to <strong>Settings</strong> &gt; <strong>Devices</strong> &gt; <strong>Bluetooth Devices</strong>.</li><li>Highlight the controller you want to reset, press the <strong>Options</strong> button, then select <strong>Forget Device</strong>.</li><li>For a hard reset, use a straightened paperclip to press the button inside the small hole on the back of the controller for five seconds.</li></ul></div><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-callout-body mntl-text-block -->
</div><!-- end: comp theme-generic mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-callout mntl-sc-block-callout mntl-block -->
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-1" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
This article explains how to reset a PS4 controller.Instructions apply to the official DualShock 4 controller.
</p><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html -->
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-2" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block -->
<span class="heading-toc" id="toc-how-to-reset-your-ps4-controller"></span> <h2 id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-3" class="comp mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class="mntl-sc-block-heading__text"> How to Reset Your PS4 Controller </span> </h2><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading -->
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-4" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
A &#34;soft reset&#34; generally refers to turning a computer or device off and then on again, which flushes out memory and can correct many issues.
</p><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html -->
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-5" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block -->
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-6" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
In doing a PS4 controller soft reset, we&#39;ll also reset the connection between the controller and the console. However, you can only do this if you have a second PS4 controller. If you don&#39;t have an extra controller, skip ahead to the directions on performing a hard reset.
</p><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html -->
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-7" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block -->
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-8" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
Follow these steps to soft reset your PS4 controller:
</p><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html -->
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-9" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block -->
<OL id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-10" class="comp mntl-sc-block-group--OL mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup"><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-group--OL mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup -->
<LI id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-11" class="comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup"><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup -->
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-12" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
Log in with your second (working) controller and navigate to the <strong>Settings</strong> in the PS4&#39;s top menu. This is the option that looks like a suitcase.
</p><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html -->
<figure id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-13" class="comp mntl-sc-block-image--no-theme mntl-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-universal-image figure-landscape figure-high-res">
