</div>
</div>
</figure><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-image--no-theme mntl-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-universal-image figure-landscape figure-high-res -->
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-30" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block -->
</LI>
<LI id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-32" class="comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup"><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup -->
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-33" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
Press the <strong>Options</strong> button on your controller, found to the right of the touchpad. This will bring up a new menu.
</p><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html -->
<figure id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-34" class="comp mntl-sc-block-image--no-theme mntl-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-universal-image figure-landscape figure-high-res">
<div class="figure-media">
<div class="img-placeholder" style="padding-bottom:66.0%;">
<img
data-src="https://www.lifewire.com/thmb/HzWWHpYuxlOdODGgHzCrNZHQRDY=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/007-how-to-reset-ps4-controller-4174025-71a5841bd5544ccabf43b30a9454c2c0.jpg"
width="1500"
height="991"
alt="A DualShock 4 controller with the Options button highlighted"
class="lazyload universal-image__image"
data-expand="300"
